annotation.TEXT: Fortunately, I got past the cheepos unscathed again.
Oh, there's Lakitu! Finally! Took you long enough to show up. Maybe ER put him later in the level because he was being too evil with his original positioning?
Sigh... Let's try this again...
Yeah, I had forgotten about the random bullets there, but still, talk about bad luck...
There's plenty of coins and bricks here. Too bad I don't have an AWESOME SPREAD GUN or something similar with me right now to tear apart the bricks with.
Looks like the cheepos stopped. That's good.
The hidden power up is in the same spot as in 7-4, but it's gonna be the Ice Beam again, which I do not want.
Haw, haw. You can't hurt me, Mr. Fire Bar! (*Sticks out tongue*)
BOING!!!
To be continued... Yo!
Very good.
Blast! I was hoping I wouldn't land on that parakoopa! But, I'm still alive, unlike when Sonia got bulleted last level.
GAAAMMMEEE!!! Of course an enemy over a pit would drop a heart.
KA-BOOOOM!!!

The other difference between C-4 and 7-4 would normally be the addition of a few bricks in the corners under these two fire bars, but they're not here for some reason, and it doesn't really matter, because they're going counterclockwise for me here (probably only for slow characters), and I've got the Varia Suit anyway.
Ah, they're Beezos this time. Alright, after I get this mushroom, I'm going to go up, up, and away!
There's a power up in one of these ? blocks, but since I think I've got every one of Link's upgrades, it'll just contain an ammo pickup.

Well, I'm not going to use both Link and Samus for C-4, so I've decided to use Link in C-1. Also, I'm surprised there wasn't a vote for a character whose name starts with "C", but I'll go with Christine here to fulfill the "C" role today anyway.
Darn it. I kind of didn't want to waste my last few hearts like that, but I didn't want that Blooper to screw me over somehow either.
Umm... Any... time... now...
There's a hidden coin block which lets you easily reach this multi-coin block above it.
I often like to use the power up block as a jumping-off point to start higher up on these elevators, but it's not really necessary.
I think at around this point, Lakitu would normally go away anyway, so I don't think I'll be seeing him again in this level.
Alright random bullets, I'm ready for you this time.
Alright, three perfect flagpole hits in a row today!
Shut up, clock. Yeah, this level only gives the player 300 seconds, which should actually be plenty.
Alright, did ER forget to put Lakitu in this level?
Hello, and welcome back to more SMB Crossover! The voting results are shown above, just like all the other times.
Yeah, I'm just going to avoid that Blooper.
Alright, Lakitu should appear any time now...

Now, normally, there's a pretty wide pit here, but since I'm using a weaker jumper, there's an additional platform in the middle of the pit to help me across. Also, I remember that there's a Hammer Bro. just on the other side...
Alright, now this level is an exact copy of 7-3, except there's a Lakitu added. He'll probably appear to pester me around when the second green springboard appears.

Nuts... I was hoping the game would restore my Magma Bazooka when I grabbed that mushroom. I think the game sometimes restores additional things you had lost upon getting hit if you get another mushroom without dying, but that didn't happen this time.
Whoa! Okay, let's try that again without missing the jump this time!
Okay, looks like I just made it. Whew.
There's a pipe here that leads to a bonus room, but I'm going to hold off on entering it for a moment.
There's another helpful additional platform here. Also, there's another hidden block with a vine block above it, so guess what? It's sky bonus time!
That one too.
Ah, it's Quick Man!
Alright, this is it, guys! I'm approaching the last world of The Lost Levels, world D! So, place your votes for who you guys want me to wrap up this game with!
I don't know if the Varia Suit will protect me from Bowser's fire or Podoboos, so I'm not going to take any chances with those.
Really, game?! A random bullet had to appear in that exact spot at that exact time?!
And I had just enough time to perfectly line up for 5000 plus six fireworks!
Oh, the fire bar immunity is so good here. It takes a lot of the risk out of this jump!
That was weird how I kicked that shell like that, but whatever. It's fine since I didn't get hurt.
The alt. skin votes include a Power Suit Samus and Sonia (Simon). Also, both Link and Samus got votes for C-4, and Sonia's vote is for C-1, C-2, or C-3.
Okay, I'm just gonna gun down Lakitu from here...
Now, for C-2, I believe I'll use Sonia... Huh, I used Sonia last time I used a Simon skin, didn't I? Well, Sonia got the vote, so she gets to play again!
3-1 votes: 1 E-1 votes: 1
Yay, I've rescued an Etecoon!
Whoa, good thing I was prepared to jump quickly there.
Now, I think I have enough time to just show the stuff to the left that that pipe skipped.
I thought there might be a hidden block there to allow Sonia to climb up and aim for the top of the flagpole.
I don't remember if I showed this off in the past (I probably did at some point), but the boomerang can collect coins! If I wasn't short on time, I could easily guarantee a perfect here!
Oh, yeah. There's more negative poison in that brick, so watch out for that.

Shell #1 went down the hole, but shell #2 didn't. I think part of the problem with the kicked shell physics in Crossover is that their horizontal speed doesn't decrease while they're in midair, which is what happens in the original games.
NOTE: "Mega Man 2 - Airman's Stage" is Capcom's song. No copyright infringement intended.
Yah! Wow, I was worried that I was gonna land on that Beezo, and I nearly fell into the pit while backing away from it!
Still no Lakitu?
There's a hidden 1-up plus sign right here, and be careful of the poison minus sign in the second ? block here.
I don't know if I have enough time to waste collecting the coins from those bricks, though.
That missile barrage was probably completely unneeded, but I've got so many missiles, I may as well use at least a few of them.
Nuts. I don't think I got that last coin that the boomerang snagged. Also, that sky bonus actually sent me backwards in the level, so I've gotta book it!
Yeah, I just wanted to collect the star from that brick, even though it's of little use since I'm going to enter the bonus room now.
And there's where I had gotten the star, so now to resume course to the right.
Whoa! Forgot that Quick Man couldn't double jump there! Luckily, I managed to land on the edge of the pipe without getting bitten.
Alright, it's boss time, against Atari Bowser!
...I'm going with a Power Suit Samus for C-4! I'll pick the SNES one.
Woo, 1.5 million points! Okay, now for C-4, let's use someone explosive. Both Link and Samus can use bombs, and I already used a Link skin for C-1, so...
Alright, for C-3, let's go with something completely random! (Or maybe just pseudo-random.)
Can someone drop a big heart, please?
I know why that red springboard is there-- in case a weaker jumper lands on that mushroom platform.
Oh, nuts. I think this is a flying cheepo level. Also, I have almost no hearts left.

Now, C-4 is an exact copy of 7-4, except for a few changes. For starters, there's an extra fire bar near the start of the level... Oh, but I don't have to worry about that because of Samus's Varia Suit! Nice!
Demo count: 14
I hope Lakitu doesn't respawn at an evil time for me...
That's it. I'm out of subweapon uses until I find more hearts.
